ctIGMP.name: ctIGMP

revisions.description: Added the IgmpProtocolClassTc, and IgmpProtocolIdTc TEXTUAL CONVENTIONS, added the ctIGMPProtocolClassificationTable.
Deprecated the ctIGMPPolicyTable and the ctIGMPStaticTable. Added ctIGMPStaticGroupTable, ctIGMPExtCacheTable, ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterTable, ctIGMPPortTable, and the ctIGMPStatsCntrs groups.
Added the ctIGMPStaticEntry Table for static multicast configuration.

ctIGMP.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 50 Minuteman Rd. Andover, MA 01810-1008 USA Phone: +1 978 684 1000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
ctIGMP.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP enterprise MIBs under the Cabletron enterprise OID pertaining to configuration of IGMP.

IgmpPortModeTc.name: IgmpPortModeTc
IgmpPortModeTc.description: This textual convention maps out possible igmp port modes.

IgmpProtocolClassTc.name: IgmpProtocolClassTc
IgmpProtocolClassTc.description: This textual convention describes the possible ways IGMP can classify received frames.

IgmpProtocolIdTc.name: IgmpProtocolIdTc
IgmpProtocolIdTc.description: Bit definitions for each of the IP protocol numbers assigned by IANA.

ctIGMPNewDefaultState.name: ctIGMPNewDefaultState
ctIGMPNewDefaultState.description: This object defines the state in which IGMP will view new VLAN IDs added to the system. A value of Enable (1), indicates that IGMP will create entries for all new VLANs in the ENABLE state. A value of Disable (2), indicates IGMP will create entries for all new VLANs in the DISABLED or 'not in service' state.

ctIGMPMibRev.name: ctIGMPMibRev
ctIGMPMibRev.description: This object defines the revision of the IGMP MIB in the firmware.

ctIGMPMibRevString.name: ctIGMPMibRevString
ctIGMPMibRevString.description: This object is a textual representation of the revision of the IGMP MIB in the firmware.

ctIGMPConfigGroupTblFullAction.name: ctIGMPConfigGroupTblFullAction
ctIGMPConfigGroupTblFullAction.description: This object defines the behavior of IGMP when its group table is full. The user may choose to send multicast frames to known routers, or flood these frames to the vlan.

ctIGMPVlanTable.name: ctIGMPVlanTable
ctIGMPVlanTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the VLANs on which IGMP is enabled.

ctIGMPVlanEntry.name: ctIGMPVlanEntry
ctIGMPVlanEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a VLAN on which IGMP is enabled.

ctIGMPVlanId.name: ctIGMPVlanId
ctIGMPVlanId.description: The VlanId value of the Vlan for which IGMP is enabled.

ctIGMPVlanQueryInterval.name: ctIGMPVlanQueryInterval
ctIGMPVlanQueryInterval.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 8.2
ctIGMPVlanQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this Vlan.

ctIGMPVlanStatus.name: ctIGMPVlanStatus
ctIGMPVlanStatus.description: The activation of a row enables IGMP on the Vlan. The destruction of a row disables IGMP on the Vlan.

ctIGMPVlanVersion.name: ctIGMPVlanVersion
ctIGMPVlanVersion.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 4
ctIGMPVlanVersion.description: The version of IGMP which is running on this Vlan. This object can be used to configure a switch capable of either value. For IGMP to function correctly, all and routers on a Vlan must be configured to run the same version of IGMP on that Vlan.

ctIGMPVlanQuerier.name: ctIGMPVlanQuerier
ctIGMPVlanQuerier.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 3
ctIGMPVlanQuerier.description: The address of the IGMP Querier on the Vlan to which this switch is attached.

ctIGMPVlanQueryMaxResponseTime.name: ctIGMPVlanQueryMaxResponseTime
ctIGMPVlanQueryMaxResponseTime.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 8.3
ctIGMPVlanQueryMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time advertised in IGMPv2 queries on this Vlan.

ctIGMPVlanRobustness.name: ctIGMPVlanRobustness
ctIGMPVlanRobustness.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 8.1
ctIGMPVlanRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a Vlan. If a Vlan is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

ctIGMPVlanLastMembQueryIntvl.name: ctIGMPVlanLastMembQueryIntvl
ctIGMPVlanLastMembQueryIntvl.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 8.8
ctIGMPVlanLastMembQueryIntvl.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages. This value may be tuned to modify the leave latency of the network. A reduced value results in reduced time to detect the loss of the last member of a group.

ctIGMPVlanQuerierUpTime.name: ctIGMPVlanQuerierUpTime
ctIGMPVlanQuerierUpTime.description: The number of seconds since ctIGMPVlanQuerier was last changed.

ctIGMPVlanQuerierExpiryTime.name: ctIGMPVlanQuerierExpiryTime
ctIGMPVlanQuerierExpiryTime.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 8.5
ctIGMPVlanQuerierExpiryTime.description: The number of seconds remaining before the Other Querier Present Timer expires. If the local system is the querier, the value of this object is zero.

ctIGMPVlanQuerierIP.name: ctIGMPVlanQuerierIP
ctIGMPVlanQuerierIP.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 7
ctIGMPVlanQuerierIP.description: The source IP address used by a switch when acting as IGMP querier for a Vlan. The value chosen must be in the valid IP address space for any attached routed interface(s) on the Vlan. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates that the switch will not act as querier for the Vlan.

ctIGMPCacheTable.name: ctIGMPCacheTable
ctIGMPCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast groups for vlans with members on a particular interface.

ctIGMPCacheEntry.name: ctIGMPCacheEntry
ctIGMPCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the ctIGMPCacheTable.

ctIGMPCacheAddress.name: ctIGMPCacheAddress
ctIGMPCacheAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

ctIGMPCacheVlanId.name: ctIGMPCacheVlanId
ctIGMPCacheVlanId.description: The VlanId for which this entry contains information.

ctIGMPCacheIfIndex.name: ctIGMPCacheIfIndex
ctIGMPCacheIfIndex.description: The interface for which this entry contains information for an IP multicast group address.

ctIGMPCacheLastReporter.name: ctIGMPCacheLastReporter
ctIGMPCacheLastReporter.description: The IP address of the source of the last membership report received for this IP Multicast group address on this interface. If no membership report has been received, this object has the value 0.0.0.0.

ctIGMPCacheUpTime.name: ctIGMPCacheUpTime
ctIGMPCacheUpTime.description: The time since the system joined this group address, or zero if the system is not currently a member.

ctIGMPCacheExpiryTime.name: ctIGMPCacheExpiryTime
ctIGMPCacheExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out.

ctIGMPCacheVersion1HostTimer.name: ctIGMPCacheVersion1HostTimer
ctIGMPCacheVersion1HostTimer.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 8.11
ctIGMPCacheVersion1HostTimer.description: The time remaining until the local switch will assume that there are no longer any IGMP version 1 members on the IP subnet attached to this interface. Upon hearing any IGMPv1 Membership Report, this value is reset to the group membership timer. While this time remaining is non-zero, the local switch ignores any IGMPv2 Leave messages for this group that it receives on this interface.

ctIGMPPolicyTable.name: ctIGMPPolicyTable
ctIGMPPolicyTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IGMP group policy for vlans with members on a particular interface.

ctIGMPPolicyEntry.name: ctIGMPPolicyEntry
ctIGMPPolicyEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the ctigmpPolicyTable.

ctIGMPPolicyAddress.name: ctIGMPPolicyAddress
ctIGMPPolicyAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information. A value of 224.0.0.0 indicates all multicast groups.

ctIGMPPolicyVlanId.name: ctIGMPPolicyVlanId
ctIGMPPolicyVlanId.description: The VlanId for which this entry contains information.

ctIGMPPolicyIfIndex.name: ctIGMPPolicyIfIndex
ctIGMPPolicyIfIndex.description: The interface for which this entry contains information for an IP multicast group address. A value of zero indicates all ports.

ctIGMPPolicyStatus.name: ctIGMPPolicyStatus
ctIGMPPolicyStatus.description: The activation of a row enables IGMP policy for this entry. The destruction of a row disables any IGMP policy for this entry.

ctIGMPPolicyInclusion.name: ctIGMPPolicyInclusion
ctIGMPPolicyInclusion.description: The IGMP policy for this entry.

ctIGMPStaticTable.name: ctIGMPStaticTable
ctIGMPStaticTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the static IGMP entries.

ctIGMPStaticEntry.name: ctIGMPStaticEntry
ctIGMPStaticEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a static entry that IGMP will act upon.

ctIGMPStaticGroupAddress.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupAddress
ctIGMPStaticGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for IGMP to send multicast data to.

ctIGMPStaticVlanId.name: ctIGMPStaticVlanId
ctIGMPStaticVlanId.description: The VlanId for IGMP to send multicast data to.

ctIGMPStaticOutPortList.name: ctIGMPStaticOutPortList
ctIGMPStaticOutPortList.description: The set of ports configured by management for this multicast group and this VLAN to which multicast group-addressed data frames are to be forwarded.

ctIGMPStaticRowStatus.name: ctIGMPStaticRowStatus
ctIGMPStaticRowStatus.description: The activation of a row creates a static entry. The destruction of a row deletes a static entry.

ctIGMPStaticGroupTable.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupTable
ctIGMPStaticGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the static IGMP entries.

ctIGMPStaticGroupEntry.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupEntry
ctIGMPStaticGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a static entry that IGMP will act upon.

ctIGMPStaticGroupIPAddress.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupIPAddress
ctIGMPStaticGroupIPAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for IGMP to send multicast data to.

ctIGMPStaticGroupVlanId.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupVlanId
ctIGMPStaticGroupVlanId.description: The VlanId for IGMP to send multicast data to.

ctIGMPStaticGroupSourceIPAddress.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupSourceIPAddress
ctIGMPStaticGroupSourceIPAddress.description: The IP source address of this entry. For IGMP Version 2, use 0.0.0.0

ctIGMPStaticGroupIncludeList.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupIncludeList
ctIGMPStaticGroupIncludeList.description: The set of ports configured by management for this multicast group and this VLAN to which multicast group-addressed data frames are to be forwarded.

ctIGMPStaticGroupExcludeList.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupExcludeList
ctIGMPStaticGroupExcludeList.description: The set of ports configured by management for this multicast group and this VLAN for which received IGMP reports will not be accepted.

ctIGMPStaticGroupRowStatus.name: ctIGMPStaticGroupRowStatus
ctIGMPStaticGroupRowStatus.description: The activation of a row creates a static entry. The destruction of a row deletes a static entry. Not in service disables a static entry

ctIGMPExtCacheTable.name: ctIGMPExtCacheTable
ctIGMPExtCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast groups for vlans with members on a particular interface. This table provides a version 3 capable ctIGMPCacheTable, with a bridge portlist leaf vs mib2 interface index.

ctIGMPExtCacheEntry.name: ctIGMPExtCacheEntry
ctIGMPExtCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the ctIGMPCacheTable.

ctIGMPExtCacheAddress.name: ctIGMPExtCacheAddress
ctIGMPExtCacheAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for this entry.

ctIGMPExtCacheSourceIPAddress.name: ctIGMPExtCacheSourceIPAddress
ctIGMPExtCacheSourceIPAddress.description: The IP source address of this entry.

ctIGMPExtCacheLastReporter.name: ctIGMPExtCacheLastReporter
ctIGMPExtCacheLastReporter.description: The IP address of the source of the last membership report received for this IP Multicast group address on this interface. If no membership report has been received, this object has the value 0.0.0.0.

ctIGMPExtCacheUpTime.name: ctIGMPExtCacheUpTime
ctIGMPExtCacheUpTime.description: The time since the system joined this group address, or zero if the system is not currently a member.

ctIGMPExtCacheExpiryTime.name: ctIGMPExtCacheExpiryTime
ctIGMPExtCacheExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out.

ctIGMPExtCacheVersion1HostTimer.name: ctIGMPExtCacheVersion1HostTimer
ctIGMPExtCacheVersion1HostTimer.reference: Network Working Group RFC2236, November 1997. Section 8.11
ctIGMPExtCacheVersion1HostTimer.description: The time remaining until the local switch will assume that there are no longer any IGMP version 1 members on the IP subnet attached to this interface. Upon hearing any IGMPv1 Membership Report, this value is reset to the group membership timer. While this time remaining is non-zero, the local switch ignores any IGMPv2 Leave messages for this group that it receives on this interface.

ctIGMPExtCacheOutPortList.name: ctIGMPExtCacheOutPortList
ctIGMPExtCacheOutPortList.description: The set of bridge ports for this multicast group, VLAN, and source IP address, to which multicast group-addressed data frames are being forwarded.

ctIGMPExtCacheSrcPort.name: ctIGMPExtCacheSrcPort
ctIGMPExtCacheSrcPort.description: The source bridge port of the multicast data stream if available

ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterTable.name: ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterTable
ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the routers seen on particular ports of a vlan through either protocol snooping or ICMP Router Discovery.

ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterEntry.name: ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterEntry
ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterEntry.description: An entry representing the routers seen on particular ports on a given vlan id.

ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterVlanId.name: ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterVlanId
ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterVlanId.description: The VlanId for IGMP to send multicast data to.

ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterPortList.name: ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterPortList
ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterPortList.description: The set of bridge ports that IGMP has seen routing protocols, IGMP queries, or ICMP Router Discovery frames on.

ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterEgressPortList.name: ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterEgressPortList
ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterEgressPortList.description: The set of bridge ports that IGMP believes has valid egress.

ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterStaticPortList.name: ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterStaticPortList
ctIGMPDiscoveredRouterStaticPortList.description: The set of bridge ports to flood all multicast frames to for this vlan id. This leaf is OPTIONAL

ctIGMPPortTable.name: ctIGMPPortTable
ctIGMPPortTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing a bridge port's bindings to multicast group addresses, vlan ids, and source addresses.

ctIGMPPortTableEntry.name: ctIGMPPortTableEntry
ctIGMPPortTableEntry.description: An entry representing the binding of bridge port to multicast group address, vlan id, and source IP address.

ctIGMPPortMode.name: ctIGMPPortMode
ctIGMPPortMode.description: The mode of the given bridge port.

ctIGMPPortTableGroupAddress.name: ctIGMPPortTableGroupAddress
ctIGMPPortTableGroupAddress.description: The multicast group address bound to this port entry.

ctIGMPPortTableVlanId.name: ctIGMPPortTableVlanId
ctIGMPPortTableVlanId.description: The vlan id bound to this port entry.

ctIGMPPortTableSourceIPAddress.name: ctIGMPPortTableSourceIPAddress
ctIGMPPortTableSourceIPAddress.description: The IP source address bound to this port entry.

ctIGMPPortTableExpireTime.name: ctIGMPPortTableExpireTime
ctIGMPPortTableExpireTime.description: The time in seconds that this port will expire in.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsGroupFull.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsGroupFull
ctIGMPStatsCntrsGroupFull.description: Flag to indicate if the group table is full(true) or not(false).

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV1QueriesSent.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV1QueriesSent
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV1QueriesSent.description: The number of IGMP Version 1 queries this device has sent out.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV2QueriesSent.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV2QueriesSent
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV2QueriesSent.description: The number of IGMP Version 2 queries this device has sent out.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesSent.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesSent
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesSent.description: The number of IGMP Version 3 queries this device has sent out.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesSent.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesSent
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesSent.description: The number of Group Specific queries this device has sent out.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumQueriesRcvd.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumQueriesRcvd
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumQueriesRcvd.description: The number of IGMP queries this device has seen from the network.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV1ReportsRcvd.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV1ReportsRcvd
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV1ReportsRcvd.description: The number of IGMP Version 1 reports this device has received.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV2ReportsRcvd.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV2ReportsRcvd
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV2ReportsRcvd.description: The number of IGMP Version 2 reports this device has received.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV3ReportsReceived.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV3ReportsReceived
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumV3ReportsReceived.description: The number of IGMP Version 3 reports this device has received.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumLeavesReceived.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumLeavesReceived
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumLeavesReceived.description: The number of IGMP leaves this device has received.

ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumDroppedFrames.name: ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumDroppedFrames
ctIGMPStatsCntrsNumDroppedFrames.description: The number of frames dropped by IGMP on this device.

ctIGMPProtocolClassificationTable.name: ctIGMPProtocolClassificationTable
ctIGMPProtocolClassificationTable.description: This table contains a listing of how IGMP will classify received IP protocol frames. For example, for a UDP multicast frame received which is IP type 17, IGMP can classify that frame in one of three ways. It can be classified as a multicast data frame, a routing protocol, or it can be ignored. A user may have a need to multicast TCP frames, but still want to send them ONLY to IGMP clients. To do this one would set protocol id 6(TCP) to 'multicastPata'

ctIGMPProtocolClassificationEntry.name: ctIGMPProtocolClassificationEntry
ctIGMPProtocolClassificationEntry.description: An entry representing the binding of IP protocol id, to the IGMP classification of a received frame.

ctIGMPProtocolClassification.name: ctIGMPProtocolClassification
ctIGMPProtocolClassification.description: The classification of this protocol id. 1 - Classify as multicast data frame. 2 - Classify as a routing protocol. 3 - Classify as Ignore.

ctIGMPProtocolIdentifier.name: ctIGMPProtocolIdentifier
ctIGMPProtocolIdentifier.description: The set of IP protocol ids to apply the classification to. Example: If this set has protocols(bits) 1 and 5 set to a '1', and the classification is 'multicastData', this will force IGMP to treat received frames with IP protocol ids of 1 and 5 as 'multicast data', and forward those frames to IGMP joined clients. Similarly if ids 1 and 5 were set to 'routing protocol' then IGMP would treat received frames with these ids as routing protocols, etc.
